<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - ADJUSTMENTS - CAB AIR
        SUSPENSION (5000 SERIES)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1600522" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CAB AIR SUSPENSION (5000 SERIES)</title>
        <para>To adjust cab ride height, measure ride height from the top of the air spring(s) to the bottom of the air
            spring(s) between the cab mount bracket and suspension crossmember bracket (
            <hotlnk document="s16005v_48.xml" xrefid="f1600588">Figure 88</hotlnk>). If dimension does not meet
            specified height of 4-1/2 inches &#177; 1/16 (114 mm) for 5000 series, adjust as necessary using the
            following procedure.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Have air system fully charged.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove one end of the height control valve linkage (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16005b3">Item 2, Figure 113</hotlnk>), loosen jam nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16005b3">Item 1, Figure 113</hotlnk>) and adjust accordingly. Tighten the jam nut on
                the valve linkage.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The height control valve arm (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16005b3">Item 3, Figure 113</hotlnk>) has a slot (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16005b3">Item 4, Figure 113</hotlnk>) which will allow for coarse adjustment also.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f16005b3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G16005E7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 113. Height Control Valve Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. JAM NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE LINKAGE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SLOT FOR COARSE ADJUSTMENT</callout1>
                <callout1>5. AIR SUPPLY AIR LINE</callout1>
                <callout1>6. AIR LINE TO AIR SPRING</callout1>
                <callout1>7. AIR LINE COMPRESSION NUT (TIGHTEN HAND TIGHT + 1 TURN)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
